# Anthroposcenic

Local image pipeline: upload → Ollama describe → configure ComfyUI → render → archive.

## Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| App | Next.js 14 App Router, React 18, TypeScript |
| UI | Tailwind CSS v4, ShadCN v4 (Radix Nova), Geist, Sonner |
| Vision | Ollama — `llava:7b` default (`config/models.json`) |
| Generation | ComfyUI — Flux GGUF default, SD checkpoints optional |
| Progress | ComfyUI WebSocket + HTTP poll; SSE to browser |

`npm run dev` starts Ollama + Next.js only. ComfyUI starts on demand during `/process`.

## UI routes

`/` → `/upload` → `/describe` → `/configure` → `/process` → `/complete` · `/archive`

Pipeline state: `sessionStorage` via `lib/pipeline-description.ts`, `lib/pipeline-config.ts` (re-exported from `lib/pipeline-storage.ts`). `imageId` in URL between steps. Archive blend uses `imageIds` → txt2img `mode=blend`.

## Key paths

- `app/api/` — thin route handlers; logic in `lib/`
- `lib/describe-route.ts` — describe SSE, `buildDescribePrompt()`
- `lib/comfyui-process-route.ts` — process SSE
- `lib/comfyui-workflow.ts` — Flux; `lib/comfyui-workflow-sd.ts` — SD
- `lib/comfyui-poll.ts` — WS + HTTP poll orchestration
- `lib/comfyui-process-stream.ts` — client process subscription + recovery
- `lib/output-archive.ts` — archive listing, safety, copy-to-upload
- `config/models.json` — Ollama default model; no custom modelfile
- `types/index.ts` — shared API/types
- `docs/` — architecture, development, API (prefer over stale comments)

## Scope

- No separate transform step; config is manual in the configure UI.
- Minimize diff scope; match existing patterns in surrounding code.
- Do not add tests unless requested.
